Bob's offer of $800,000 is significantly below both your valuation and your opening offer. Accepting would mean a substantial loss. It's highly unlikely he's unaware the product is worth significantly more to you. This indicates there's room for negotiation. You have the security of John's offer, so it's worth countering and seeing if you can reach a more agreeable price with Bob.
